            <note>Defective at the beginning and at the end. Lacuna after folios 16, 33, 49, 78, 81, 82, 85, 87, 113 ,116. Several leaves more or less damaged.</note>
            <note>An entry with the date 5525 (1765) as the time when the manuscript to which this page belonged originally was finished, folio 124r.
								Yedidyah Shelomoh Nasi ben Amtsiyahu Yosef Nasi: inscribed in an owner's entry, folio 17r.
								Shelomoh ben Eliyahu Ḥazan: inscribed, folio 122v.A note on the number of persons to be called up at the reading of the Torah, folio 17v.An English description of the manuscript in pencil, in a modern hand: folio [iii verso].</note>
